Lbl CODE
//DVD,WindowsXP

//declarations
//stores the DVD sprite into SPRITE. Sprite num is what sprite is currently selected.
DVD->SPRITE
//0 is DVD; 1 is Windows XP
0->SPRITENUM
0->CORNER
2->X
2->Y
0->YOFFSET
0->XOFFSET
1->XVEL
1->YVEL

//starts graphics and sets the background to black
det(0
SetTextFGColor(107
SetTextXY(100,1
FillScreen(0)

//repeates until clear is pressed
Repeat getKey(15)
	//draws the sprite on the buffer, then displays the buffer
	SetDraw(1
	FillScreen(0
	SetTextFGColor(107
	PrintStringXY("Corners hit: ",1,1
	PrintInt(CORNER,3
	Sprite_NoClip(SPRITE,X,Y
	SwapDraw
	//Pause 300
	//updates x and y positions with their current velocity
	XVEL+X->X
	YVEL+Y->Y
	
		//debug stuff
	If getKey(1)
		dbd(0
	End


		
	
	//if it hits a side, make it go the other way with a 
	If (X-XOFFSET)>219 or (X-XOFFSET)<1
		~1*XVEL->XVEL

		randInt(~1*(YOFFSET>~10 and Y>1),(YOFFSET<10 and Y<139))->YOFFSET+Y->Y
		If Y>140
			SetDraw(0
		SetTextFGColor(160
		PrintStringXY("Y Error! Resetting!",1,12
		For(A,1,200000,1
			End

			randInt(5,130->Y
			0->YOFFSET
		End
		
				
	End
	//if it hits top or bottom, make it go the other way 
	If (Y-YOFFSET)>139 or (Y-YOFFSET)<1
		~1*YVEL->YVEL
		randInt(~1*(XOFFSET>~10 and X>1),(XOFFSET<10 and X<219))->XOFFSET+X->X
		
		If X>220
			SetDraw(0
		SetTextFGColor(160
		PrintStringXY("X Error! Resetting!",1,12
		For(A,1,200000,1
			End
			randInt(5,210)->X
			0->XOFFSET

		End
		
			
		
	End
	
	//detects if you hit the corner
	If (X=219 and (Y=1 or Y=219)) or (X=1 and (Y=1 or Y=219))
		
		1+CORNER->CORNER
		If CORNER=999
			det(1
			Disp "Fine. You win."
			Pause 
			Return
		End
	End

	

	
	//changes the sprite if enter is pressed
	If getKey(9)
		If SPRITENUM=0
			1->SPRITENUM
			WINDOWSXP->SPRITE
		Else
			0->SPRITENUM
			DVD->SPRITE
		End
	End
End
det(1
//quits
Return

Lbl SPRITES
//100x100 sprites
DefineSprite(100,100,"")->DVD
DefineSprite(100,100,"")->WINDOWSXP
Goto CODE
